  subheading: 'Navigating Chapter 85, AI Hardware, and Encryption Device Classification for Silicon Valley Importers.',
  intro: 'California technology importers face unprecedented HTS classification complexity as semiconductors, AI accelerators, and encryption-enabled devices blur traditional tariff categories. With CBP intensifying enforcement at Los Angeles/Long Beach and Oakland ports—where 40% of U.S. containerized imports arrive—misclassification can trigger retroactive duty assessments, penalties under 19 U.S.C. § 1592, and supply chain disruptions. Silicon Valley companies importing GPUs, neural processing units, and quantum computing components must navigate both HTS Chapter 85 ambiguities and overlapping export control restrictions that affect classification determinations.',
